TY  - JOUR
AU  - Murfin, Justin
AU  - Spiegel, Matthew
T1  - Is the Risk of Sea Level Rise Capitalized in Residential Real Estate?
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhz134
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 33
IS  - 3
SP  - 1217
EP  - 1255
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a comprehensive database of coastal home sales merged with data on elevation relative to local tides, we compare prices for houses based on their inundation threshold under projections of sea level rise. The analysis separates the sensitivity of housing to rising seas from other confounding characteristics by exploiting cross-sectional differences in relative sea level rise due to vertical land motion. This provides variation in the expected time to inundation for properties of similar elevation and distance from the coast. In a variety of specifications and test settings, we find precisely estimated null results suggesting limited price effects.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhz134
ER  - 



