TY  - JOUR
AU  - Barnett, Michael
AU  - Brock, William
AU  - Hansen, Lars Peter
T1  - Pricing Uncertainty Induced by Climate Change
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhz144
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 33
IS  - 3
SP  - 1024
EP  - 1066
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Geophysicists examine and document the repercussions for the earth’s climate induced by alternative emission scenarios and model specifications. Using simplified approximations, they produce tractable characterizations of the associated uncertainty. Meanwhile, economists write highly stylized damage functions to speculate about how climate change alters macroeconomic and growth opportunities. How can we assess both climate and emissions impacts, as well as uncertainty in the broadest sense, in social decision-making? We provide a framework for answering this question by embracing recent decision theory and tools from asset pricing, and we apply this structure with its interacting components to a revealing quantitative illustration.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhz144
ER  - 



